\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*

ðŸ› ï¸ **Getting Started**

Download \& Go: Clone or download this repository to your local machine.

Add Your Assets: Place your resume PDF and a video file inside the /assets folder. Make sure their names match the project structure or update the links in index.html.

Customize Your Content: All your personal data is stored in a single JavaScript object at the bottom of the index.html file. Simply edit the let data = { ... }; object to add your skills, projects, and achievements.

Note: Changes made directly on the webpage are temporary. To make them permanent, you must edit the data object in index.html.

&nbsp;\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*

ðŸŒ **How to Deploy**

Deploying your portfolio is a breeze with GitHub Pages.

Create a New Repository: On GitHub, create a new repository and upload all your files to it.

Enable GitHub Pages:

Navigate to your repository's Settings > Pages.

Set the Branch to main and the folder to /root.

Click Save.

Live!: Your site will be live within minutes at https://your-username.github.io/your-repository-name.
